module.exports = {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"John D Potts","author":"John Potts"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"C:/Users/John/programming/gatsby-starter-blog/src/pages/2018-07-22-debugging-4/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-fe7bf.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 420px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.64999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Debugging\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-2d9c5.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-905e5.jpg 105w,\n/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-3a98f.jpg 210w,\n/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-2d9c5.jpg 420w,\n/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-64cc3.jpg 630w,\n/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-19d8a.jpg 840w,\n/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-a8185.jpg 1260w,\n/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-fe7bf.jpg 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">network</code> tab in Chrome dev tools offers a number of troubleshooting helpers for sniffing out problems with page load and network requests.\nThis tab displays a waterfall detailing how long a page takes to load, and the time each resource contributes to that load time.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/waterfall-7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a-2ac7b.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 420px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 52.88852725793328%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Network Tab\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/waterfall-7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a-bdbf1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/waterfall-7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a-f5859.png 105w,\n/static/waterfall-7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a-0926c.png 210w,\n/static/waterfall-7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a-bdbf1.png 420w,\n/static/waterfall-7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a-ebc58.png 630w,\n/static/waterfall-7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a-ca585.png 840w,\n/static/waterfall-7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a-2ac7b.png 1229w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>You can see if large JS files, images, or other large requests are causing your page speed to lag. You can also view snapshots with a visual history of your page load in this tab.</p>\n<p>Another useful feature of the network tab is the ability to view a site while simulating a slow connection. The downward arrow at the far left lets the user select from a number of speeds; try selecting <code class=\"language-text\">slow 3g</code> and reloading the page- this is how the page loads for users with slow 3G connections.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/speed-91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2-fbefb.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 307px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 72.9641693811075%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Network throttle\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/speed-91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2-fbefb.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/speed-91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2-b614f.png 105w,\n/static/speed-91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2-6a4f0.png 210w,\n/static/speed-91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2-fbefb.png 307w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 307px) 100vw, 307px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The network tab also gives a ton of details about network requests that are being made. You can filter requests by type, view request and response headers for a particular request, and the timing of that request.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/headers-91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e-eb3cc.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 420px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 34.87348734873487%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Headers Tab\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/headers-91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e-bdbf1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/headers-91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e-f5859.png 105w,\n/static/headers-91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e-0926c.png 210w,\n/static/headers-91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e-bdbf1.png 420w,\n/static/headers-91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e-ebc58.png 630w,\n/static/headers-91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e-ca585.png 840w,\n/static/headers-91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e-eb3cc.png 909w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p> You can also choose to block a particular request or domain and reload the page, simulating the outage of an API.</p>\n<p>This concludes my four-part series on Dev tools: stay tuned for another post coming soon that will detail some of the lesser-known tabs in Chrome Dev Tools!</p>","excerpt":"The   tab in Chrome dev tools offers a number of troubleshooting helpers for sniffing out problems with page load and network requests.\nThis…","fields":{"slug":"/2018-07-22-debugging-4/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Front End Debugging 4: Network Tab and More","date":"July 22, 2018","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"src":"/static/debugging4-64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015-75c44.jpg"}}}}}},"pathContext":{"slug":"/2018-07-22-debugging-4/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-07-19-debugging-3/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Front End Debugging: Working with Javascript in Chrome Dev Tools"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-07-25-cron-jobs/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"A Three-Minute Guide to Cron Jobs"}}}}


